### Context File Naming & Archiving Refinement

Status: Complete  
Owner: Implementer  
Priority: High  
Effort: Small

## Objective

Clarify and enforce consistent naming conventions for scoped context files and establish archiving patterns for completed work.

## Task Context

- Current state:
  - `Plans.inventory` incorrectly tracks `.task` files instead of `.plan` files
  - Naming convention for scoped files not fully documented
  - No clear archiving pattern for completed context files
  
- Desired state:
  - `Plans.inventory` only lists `.plan` files
  - Clear pattern: `{Name}.{ContextFileType}.{Scope}.{extension}`
  - Archiving convention: slice-level `archive/` directories

## Task Deliverables

- D1: `Planning/Plans.inventory` - Corrected to track only `.plan` files
- D2: `Planning/ContextFiles.md` - Document `*.{ContextFileType}.{Scope}.{extension}` pattern with examples
- D3: `Planning/Plan.plan.template` - Use `{PlanName}.plan.Tasks.inventory` naming
- D4: Archiving convention added to relevant docs

## Architecture Decisions

- AD-1: Use `{Name}.{Type}.{Scope}.{Ext}` pattern — Rationale: Clear, parseable, self-documenting file relationships
- AD-2: Slice-level `archive/` directories — Rationale: Keep archives close to active work, easy discovery
- AD-3: Plans.inventory tracks only .plan files — Rationale: Plans are high-level; tasks are tracked in plan-specific inventories

## Success Criteria

- [ ] Plans.inventory contains only `.plan` file references (currently empty until plans created)
- [ ] All documentation uses correct naming pattern
- [ ] Examples demonstrate scoped file naming
- [ ] Archiving pattern documented

